---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Wyoming's Role in America's Energy Future" description="Examining how Wyoming's regulatory framework and natural resources position the state as a leader in next-generation energy infrastructure.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative bg-navy-950 text-white">
    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24">
      <div class="mb-6">
        <a href="/insights" class="inline-flex items-center text-sm text-gold-500 hover:text-gold-400 transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          Back to Insights
        </a>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-6">
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-gold-500">Policy</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400">•</span>
          <time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2025-01-15">January 15, 2025</time>
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-6">
          Wyoming's Role in America's Energy Future
        </h1>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          Examining how Wyoming's regulatory framework and natural resources position the state as a leader in next-generation energy infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-gold-600 via-gold-500 to-gold-600"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article Content -->
  <article class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-700 leading-relaxed font-serif mb-8">
          Wyoming stands at a critical inflection point in American energy development. The state's combination of abundant natural resources, forward-thinking regulatory framework, and established industrial infrastructure creates a unique environment for next-generation energy projects.
        </p>

        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-12 mb-6">Regulatory Leadership</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Wyoming's achievement of Class VI primacy for CO₂ storage represents more than a regulatory milestone—it demonstrates the state's commitment to enabling responsible carbon management infrastructure. This regulatory clarity reduces project risk and accelerates development timelines for carbon-managed industrial facilities.
        </p>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-12 mb-6">Resource Abundance</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          As the nation's leading coal producer, Wyoming possesses energy-dense feedstocks ideally suited for modern gasification and carbon conversion processes. When combined with proven geological formations for CO₂ storage, these resources enable integrated industrial platforms that convert domestic energy into strategic manufacturing capacity.
        </p>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-12 mb-6">Industrial Infrastructure</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Existing rail networks, pipeline corridors, and industrial workforce capabilities provide the foundation for large-scale project execution. This infrastructure reduces capital requirements and de-risks development timelines—critical factors for institutional investors evaluating multi-billion dollar commitments.
        </p>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-12 mb-6">Strategic Positioning</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Wyoming's pro-business climate, combined with federal emphasis on domestic manufacturing and energy security, positions the state as a natural hub for coal-to-products facilities. Projects developed under this framework strengthen supply chains, create high-wage employment, and reinforce America's industrial independence.
        </p>

        <!-- Conclusion -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-gold-500 p-8 mt-12">
          <p class="text-lg text-navy-900 font-semibold leading-relaxed">
            Wyoming's energy future is not about preserving legacy industries—it's about transforming proven resources through modern technology and disciplined execution into the manufacturing infrastructure America requires.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- Related Content / CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-slate-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white border-t-4 border-gold-500 p-8 shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-gold-700 mb-4">Learn More</h3>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-4">The Cheyenne CC2A Project</h4>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
            See how CapStone is advancing Wyoming's coal-to-ammonia infrastructure with integrated carbon management.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/project"
            class="inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-navy-900 hover:text-gold-700 transition-colors uppercase tracking-wide"
          >
            View Project Details
            <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-navy-950 text-white p-8">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-gold-500 mb-4">Questions?</h3>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Connect With Our Team</h4>
          <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6">
            Discuss Wyoming energy opportunities and CapStone's development platform.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-gold-600 hover:bg-gold-500 text-navy-950 font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase text-sm transition-colors"
          >
            Contact Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
